[enriched] > Query written to `query05.preql` and validated with `trilogy run query05.preql`. The query:
[enriched] > 
[enriched] > 1. Imports `raw.all_sales` which unifies store/catalog/web channels and their returns
[enriched] > 2. Uses a multi-select (`merge ... align ... derive`) pattern:
[enriched] >    - **Sales side**: filters by sale date in range (Aug 23 - Sep 6, 2000) and non-null `channel_dim_id`, groups by channel type label ('store channel'/'catalog channel'/'web channel') and entity ID (prefix+text_id) using ROLLUP for subtotals/grand total
[enriched] >    - **Return side**: filters by return date in range and non-null `return_channel_dim_id`, groups by channel type + return entity ID with ROLLUP
[enriched] >    - **Align**: aligns both sides on channel and entity columns (NULL rows represent subtotal/total levels)
[enriched] >    - **Derive**: coalesces nulls to 0 and computes net_profit = sales_profit - return_loss
[enriched] > 3. Orders by channel then entity (NULLs first = totals above details)
[enriched] > 4. Limits to 100 rows
[enriched] > 
[enriched] > Key results: grand total, channel subtotals per channel, and individual entity rows showing gross sales (ext_sales_price), total returns (return_amount), and net profit after subtracting return net losses.
