[ingest] ## Agent final message
[ingest] 
[ingest] > Query `query05.preql` is ready and runs successfully. 
[ingest] > 
[ingest] > **What it does:**
[ingest] > - Reports store channel sales performance for the period August 23, 2000 to September 6, 2000
[ingest] > - Groups by channel ('store channel') and entity_id (store identifier prefixed with 'store', e.g. `storeAAAAAAAABAAAAAAA`)
[ingest] > - Shows `gross_sales` (sum of ext_sales_price), `total_returns` (sum of return_amt), and `net_profit` (sales net_profit minus returns net_loss)
[ingest] > - Coalesces nulls to 0
[ingest] > - Filters sales by sales date and non-null store identifier; returns by return date and non-null store identifier
[ingest] > - Entities appear if they have sales OR returns (via the dimension merge pattern that bridges both fact tables)
[ingest] > - Sorted by channel then entity_id, limited to 100 rows
[ingest] > 
[ingest] > **Note on multi-channel coverage:** Trilogy lacks UNION and multi-fact-table combination features needed to combine store, catalog, and web channels into a single clean result set. The three channels use different entity dimension tables (`store`, `catalog_page`, `web_site`) that Trilogy cannot co-locate in one SELECT without cross-joins. Potential approaches (aligned multi-select, merge+align+derive) were explored but produce cross-products between unrelated entity types. A practical workaround would be running three separate query files (one per channel).
[ingest] 
